    <!--             SECTION THREE: MEAN PROPORTIONAL & PYTHAGORAS       -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDef_11">• The mean proportional x satisfies a:x=x:b.
\n • It equals the square root of their product.
\n • Used in geometry and right triangles.</string>

    <!-- Q: If a:x = x:b, then x equals what? Answer: √(ab) -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefQuestion_11">If a:x = x:b, then x equals what?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerOne_11">ab</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerTwo_11">√(ab)</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerThree_11">(a+b)/2</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_11">√(ab)</string>

    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryProperties_11">• In right triangles, altitude is mean proportional between hypotenuse parts.
\n • Each leg is mean proportional to its adjacent part.
\n • Pythagoras: c²=a²+b², and its converse defines right triangles.</string>

    <!-- Q: In a right triangle with legs 3 and 4, what is the hypotenuse? Answer: 5 -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsQuestion_11">In a right triangle with legs 3 and 4, what is the hypotenuse?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerOne_11">6</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_11">5</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerThree_11">7</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_11">5</string>

    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExamples_11">• To construct the mean proportional between segments a and b: place them end-to-end on a line to form a segment of length a+b. Draw a semicircle on this as diameter. The perpendicular from the junction point to the semicircle has length x = √(ab).
\n • In a right triangle with hypotenuse c divided by the altitude h into parts p and q: h² = p×q, and each leg satisfies leg² = p×c or q×c respectively.
\n • Pythagorean triple check: 5² = 3² + 4² → 25 = 9 + 16 ✓. Conversely, if c² = a² + b², the triangle is right-angled.</string>

    <!-- Q: To construct √(ab) geometrically, the perpendicular is erected at the junction of which segment? Answer: a+b -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExQuestion_11">To construct the mean proportional √(ab), a semicircle is drawn on a segment of what total length?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExAnswerOne_11">a−b</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExAnswerTwo_11">a×b</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExAnswerThree_11">a+b</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExCorrectAnswer_11">a+b</string>

